OL,3,CCourt of Appeal rejects bid to
OL,4,Cincrease sentence of couple who
OL,5,Cmurdered grandson
OL,7,FEthan had been placed on the child
OL,8,Fprotection register, requiring him to
OL,9,Fbe seen every 10 days, but when his
OL,10,Fmother last saw her social worker, on
OL,11,FAugust 5, she spoke to him on the
OL,12,Fdoorstep and told him Ethan was having
OL,13,Fa nap.
OL,15,FLord Justice Popplewell continued: "On
OL,16,Fbehalf of the Solicitor General, Mr
OL,17,FJones contends that for Michael and
OL,18,FKerry the minimum terms of 23 years,
OL,19,Fand 17 years, respectively, were
OL,20,Funduly lenient."
OL,26,@wD@dOU|D@PO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/16
